HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 991
By Clemmons
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Judge John P. Brown of
Nashville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Judge John P. Brown of Nashville; and
WHEREAS, a Nashville native, John Brown was born on January 6, 1942, to J.P. and
Hazel Spillers Brown; he was a 1960 graduate of Hillsboro High School, where he met his first
wife, Lolann Wamser Brown; and
WHEREAS, after graduating from the University of Tennessee at Memphis Pharmacy
School in 1964, Mr. Brown joined the family business, J.P. Brown Drugstores, where he had
worked the counter and soda fountain as a young man; he opened his store on Hillsboro Road
and helped build J.P. Brown Drugstores into Nashville's largest independent pharmacy; and
WHEREAS, John Brown soon decided to pivot, attending the Nashville YMCA Law
School and obtaining his Juris Doctorate in 1969; he practiced law for many years, handling a
variety of civil and criminal matters at his law office in Green Hills while being active in local
politics; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Brown was elected to serve as judge of Davidson County General
Sessions Court Division V in 1982 and served in that position until his retirement from the bench
in 2006; and
WHEREAS, Judge John Brown was a compassionate and wise jurist, beloved by the
courthouse crowd for his southern drawl and folksy humor; during his tenure, he played an
integral role in bringing Courts into the computer age, serving on the Justice Information System
Committee for many years; and
